             Mitsui & Co. may take a charge of
several billion yen for the quarter ended in June related to
losses from BP Plcâ€™s oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico, Nikkei
English News reported, without saying how it obtained the
information.  
 The company holds a partial stake in the oil well through a
subsidiary of Mitsui Oil Exploration Co., Nikkei reported.
Mitsui has decided to write off the investment because the well
is not expected to produce revenue in the future, Nikkei said.  
          
          


  


        